  "prompt": "What is 3E - 3 tier AC in Duronto?",
  "response": "In the context of Indian Railways, \"3E\" refers to \"Three-Tier Economy\" class accommodation on Duronto Express trains. Duronto Express trains are known for their faster travel between major cities with fewer stops compared to normal express trains. \n\nThe \"3E\" class is designed to be a more affordable option compared to the standard three-tier AC coaches (which are typically denoted as \"3AC\"). The economy coaches generally have slightly less space and fewer amenities than the regular 3AC coaches, making them a budget-friendly choice for travelers looking for air-conditioned comfort.\n\n\"3 Tier\" usually refers to the standard three-tier AC configuration, which includes three levels of berths (upper, middle, and lower) in each compartment, while \"3E\" is a more economical version of this class.\n\nIf you're considering traveling on a Duronto Express train, you can choose the 3E class for a lower fare while still enjoying the benefits of air conditioning and reserved seating.",
